documentation.title: Chat Messages
documentation.description: Retrieve chat messages.

documentation.title: Destination
documentation.description: Representation of a messaging destination. Can be ID or channel name, depending on the provider capability.

documentation.title: After Timestamp
documentation.description: Retrieve only messages after the given UNIX timestamp (in milliseconds, e.g. 1095379198750)

documentation.title: Before Timestamp
documentation.description: Retrieve only messages before the given UNIX timestamp (in milliseconds, e.g. 1095379198750)

documentation.title: Limit
documentation.description: Maximum number of messages to retrieve in one page

documentation.title: Page
documentation.description: Identification of page with paginated results (cursor)

documentation.title: Get chat messages
documentation.description: Retrieve paginated list of messages

documentation.title: Id
documentation.description: Unique identifier of the attachment

documentation.title: Created At
documentation.description: UNIX timestamp (in milliseconds, e.g. 1095379198750) when the attachment was created

documentation.title: File Name
documentation.description: Name of attached file

documentation.title: Media Type
documentation.description: MIME type of the attached file

documentation.title: Url
documentation.description: Source url of the attachment

documentation.title: Id
documentation.description: Unique identifier of the message

documentation.title: Author
documentation.description: Author of retrieved message. Contains ID and username, depending on the provider capability.

documentation.title: Created At
documentation.description: UNIX timestamp (in milliseconds, e.g. 1095379198750) when the message was created

documentation.title: URL
documentation.description: URL address pointing to retrieved message.

documentation.title: Has Thread
documentation.description: Boolean that represents whether message is parent to some thread

documentation.title: Thread Id
documentation.description: If the message was sent to a thread, identifies the parent thread by its Id.

documentation.title: Text
documentation.description: Contents of the retrieved message

documentation.title: Updated At
documentation.description: UNIX timestamp (in milliseconds, e.g. 1095379198750) when the message was last updated

documentation.title: Reactions
documentation.description:
List of reactions on retrieved message. Each reaction contains emoji string containing encoded emoji,
number of reactions and list of users (IDs or usernames, depending on the provider capability)

documentation.title: Attachments
documentation.description: List of attachments in retrieved message. Contains

documentation.title: Messages
documentation.description: List of retrieved messages

documentation.title: Next Page
documentation.description: Cursor to the next page for pagination forwards

documentation.title: Rate Limit
documentation.description: Rate limit details.

documentation.title: Title
documentation.description: A short, human-readable summary of the problem type.

documentation.title: Detail
documentation.description: A human-readable explanation specific to this occurrence of the problem.

documentation.title: Rate Limit
documentation.description: Rate limit details.

documentation.title: Bucket
documentation.description:
Different parts of API may have different rate limits.
Bucket identifies to which part of API the rate limits apply.

documentation.title: Total Requests
documentation.description: Total requests available in the time window.

documentation.title: Remaining Requests
documentation.description: Remaining requests available in the time window.

documentation.title: Remaining Requests available in percents
documentation.description: Remaining requests available in the time window in percents.

documentation.title: Reset Timestamp
documentation.description: Unix timestamp when the rate limits will reset (in milliseconds).

documentation.title: Reset After
documentation.description: Number of seconds until reset of rate limit

documentation.title: Retry After
documentation.description: Number of seconds until user can retry the request
